	<li class="cat-item cat-item-186"><a href="http://www.bcgs.ca/?cat=186" title="British Columbia Heritage Glimpses


British Columbia has a fascinating history. Many stories about past British Columbia people are remembered, commemorated and celebrated today, on-line, on paper or in poetry and song. From time to time, a few of these stories will be added here for your enjoyment. 

And various British Columbia places will be featured here as well - with links to useful genealogical and historical sources on-line and in print. 

Kelowna, BC, Canada: A Brief Guide to Selected Genealogy Research Sources

Links to genealogical Guides for both Vancouver, BC and Victoria, BC are on the BCGS - Research Projects page 

">BC Heritage Glimpses</a>
</li>
	<li class="cat-item cat-item-57"><a href="http://www.bcgs.ca/?cat=57" title="British Columbia annual Awards include the BCGS Family History Book Awards and the Most Improved Genealogist Award. Follow these links to learn more about these. 

