	<li class="cat-item cat-item-5"><a href="http://www.bcgs.ca/?cat=5" title="From time to time, both new and old genealogy or history related publications and book events are featured. These may be books from the Walter Draycott Library&#039;s collections, or the BCGS&#039; own publications, or new or old books about British Columbia history or some aspect of genealogy.  

We welcome suggestions and articles for these features and, for new and upcoming books, the BCGS quarterly journal,  The British Columbia Genealogist, regularly publishes book reviews. To see a selection of past book reviews, go to our Book Review page.

Please send information about relevant book events to the BCGS Editor: Editor @ bcgs.ca">Books</a>
</li>
	<li class="cat-item cat-item-16"><a href="http://www.bcgs.ca/?cat=16" title="
The BCGS Boutique

British Columbia Genealogical Society&#039;s Boutique volunteers attend meetings and events with all kinds of genealogy and family history related items for sale - books, charts, maps, scrapbooking supplies, magnifiers, even needlework kits. 

For more information about all that&#039;s available, or to book the Boutique for an event, see the main BCGS Boutique page.">Boutique</a>
</li>
	<li class="cat-item cat-item-138"><a href="http://www.bcgs.ca/?cat=138" title="The British Columbia Genealogical Society&#039;s DNA Group for Genetic Genealogy meets periodically, usually in sessions at BCGS General Meetings. 

If you have a burning question, do not hesitate to contact the BCGS DNA Group facilitator by e-mail: diane_rogers@shaw.ca or you may leave a message at the BCGS Library: 604 502 9119

In the meantime, you will find answers to many DNA genealogy related questions at the International Society of Genealogy Genealogy (ISOGG) website, particularly in the Newbies and Resources sections: http://www.isogg.org">DNA Group News</a>
</li>
