	<li class="cat-item cat-item-53"><a href="http://www.bcgs.ca/?cat=53" title="Genealogy and Family History Events - British Columbia and Beyond

This list includes events, seminars, conferences and the like (not BCGS or other regular Meetings). Please forward information on upcoming events to the BCGS Editor editor@bcgs.ca and we will be pleased to include them in our on-line and printed publications. 

CANADA

British Columbia

18 January 2016 - Attaching Sources, Photos and Stories to Family Tree, Surrey Family History Centre, 10 —11:30 am + Practice lab in Center until 1 PM. Sign up: email: surreyfhc@gmail.com Please see this .pdf announcement for details.
6270 - 126 St. Surrey, BC. Watch for news of Family History Centre sessions in February and May. 

February 20, 2016 - Genealogy Road Show, 1-4 pm. Volunteers from the BCGS offer advice to individuals and family members researching their family history. 
Cloverdale Library, 5642 - 176A Street Surrey, BC . Bring your research details to date. Beginners receive advice on where to begin their research, based on their knowledge and family documents. Cloverdale Library will be offering tours and training on the new ViewScan for microformat digital copying.
No registration fee but register in person at the Cloverdale Library, call 604-598-7327, or email familyhistory@surrey.ca

5 March 2016 - All Day Seminar, Campbell River Genealogy Society Looking for Family in All the Right Places with Joyce Young. 
Maritime Heritage Centre, Rotary Hall.

10 April 2016 - Kelowna and District Genealogical Society Seminar with Christine Woodcock Scottish Research. 

22 April 2016 - Qualicum Beach Family History Society Presents Researching in Scotland and Ireland with Chris Paton.
Quality Inn Resort Bayside, Parksville, BC.

23 April 2016 - Qualicum Beach Family History Society International Conference with speakers Colleen Fitzgerald and Chris Paton. 
The Beach Club Resort, Parksville, BC.

27 April 2016 - Vernon Family History Society Seminar - Speaker Chris Paton. Vernon, BC. Details soon. 

30 April 2016 - BCGS Seminar with Chris Paton. Tickets available now!  For topics and registration details, see the webpage above.
South Arm United Church, South Arm United Church, 11051 No. 3 Road, Richmond, BC, 

14 May 2016 - Abbotsford Family History Day, 8:30 am to 3:30 pm. Free.  Watch for details soon at www.abbotsfordfamilyhistory.com
Abbotsford Stake Center, 30635 Blueridge Dr., Abbotsford, BC.  

23-25 September 2016 -  “Harvest Your Family Tree” Conference, Kelowna &amp; District Genealogical Society.
Kelowna, BC.  Details soon at  Kelowna and District Genealogical Society 


